From fa98563b20251d4327557b8514bb93ddd949d624 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
Date: Thu, 10 Apr 2025 23:26:19 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] mac80211: Fix GHz Band capabilities IE advertisement

While adding 6GHz band capabilities, interface support and channel
is list is validated to confirm whether 6GHz is supported.
But in single wiphy, all the interfaces will have all the supported
channels. Due to this validation, mesh beacons adds
6 GHZ Band capabilities in beacon for 5GHz as well.

Fix it by adding 6 GHz band check before adding the IE.

Signed-off-by: Ramya Gnanasekar <quic_rgnanase@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
---
 net/mac80211/mlme.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/mlme.c b/net/mac80211/mlme.c
index d18da95..6bbe453 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/mlme.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/mlme.c
@@ -1666,7 +1666,8 @@ ieee80211_add_link_elems(struct ieee80211_sub_if_data *sdata,
 		ieee80211_put_he_cap(skb, sdata, sband,
 				     &assoc_data->link[link_id].conn);
 		ADD_PRESENT_EXT_ELEM(WLAN_EID_EXT_HE_CAPABILITY);
-		ieee80211_put_he_6ghz_cap(skb, sdata, smps_mode);
+		if (sband->band == NL80211_BAND_6GHZ)
+			ieee80211_put_he_6ghz_cap(skb, sdata, smps_mode);
 	}
 
 	/*
